    • Method Detail

      • setInitialTokens

        void setInitialTokens​(List<NamedToken> tokens)
        Clear the internal token registry and repopulate it with the given collection of tokens.

        The tokens may be a mix of public and internal tokens.

        Parameters:
        tokens - The set of initial tokens to populate this token holder with.
        Throws:
        NonUniqueTokenException - If there are duplicate names or ids amongst the given tokens.

      • addToken

        void addToken​(NamedToken token)
        Add the given token to the internal token registry. The token maybe be either a public or an internal one.
        Parameters:
        token - The token to add.
        Throws:
        NonUniqueTokenException - if the token conflicts with an existing token on id, or on name.

      • getOrCreateId

        int getOrCreateId​(String name)
           throws KernelException
        Get the id of the public token by the given name, or create a new id for the token if it does not have one already, and then return that id.

        This method is thread-safe, and will ensure that distinct tokens will not have multiple ids allocated for them.

        Parameters:
        name - The name of the token to get the id for.
        Returns:
        The (possibly newly created) id of the given token.
        Throws:
        KernelException

      • getOrCreateIds

        void getOrCreateIds​(String[] names,
                    int[] ids)
             throws KernelException
        Resolve the ids of the given token names into the array for ids.

        Any tokens that don't already have an id will have one created for it.

        Note that this only looks at public tokens. For internal tokens, use getOrCreateInternalIds(String[], int[]).

        Throws:
        KernelException

      • getTokenById

        NamedToken getTokenById​(int id)
                 throws TokenNotFoundException
        Get the (public) token that has the given id, or throw TokenNotFoundException.

        The exception will be thrown even if an internal token exists with that id.

        To get an internal token, see getInternalTokenById(int).

        Throws:
        TokenNotFoundException

      • getIdByName

        int getIdByName​(String name)
        Returns the id, or TokenConstants.NO_TOKEN if no token with this name exists.

      • getIdsByNames

        boolean getIdsByNames​(String[] names,
                      int[] ids)
        Resolve the ids of the given token names into the array for ids.

        Any tokens that don't already have an id will not be resolved, and the corresponding entry in the ids array will be left untouched. If you wish for those unresolved id entries to end up with the TokenConstants.NO_TOKEN value, you must first fill the array with that value before calling this method.

        This method will not resolve internal tokens; only public ones.

        Returns:
        true if some of the token names could not be resolved, false otherwise.

      • getAllTokens

        Iterable<NamedToken> getAllTokens()
        Get an iterator of all public tokens. No internal tokens are returned by this iterator.

      • getTokenType

        String getTokenType()
        Get the type of the tokens held in this holder.
        Returns:
        the type of tokens in this holder.

      • hasToken

        boolean hasToken​(int id)
        Tests whether or not the given token id is in use.
        Parameters:
        id - the id to test for.
        Returns:
        true if the given token id is in use.

      • size

        int size()
        Returns:
        the number of public tokens currently in this token holder.

      • getOrCreateInternalIds

        void getOrCreateInternalIds​(String[] names,
                            int[] ids)
                     throws KernelException
        This is the same as getOrCreateIds(String[], int[]), but for internal tokens.

        This method does not take public tokens into consideration.

        Throws:
        KernelException

      • getInternalTokenById

        NamedToken getInternalTokenById​(int id)
                         throws TokenNotFoundException
        This is the same as getTokenById(int), but for internal tokens.

        The TokenNotFoundException exception will be thrown even if a public token exists with that id.

        Throws:
        TokenNotFoundException
